{{Branches of the visual arts}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Light Art}} [[Category:Light art|*]]

A '''studio potter''' is one who is a modern artist or artisan, who either works alone or in a small group, producing unique items of [[pottery]] in small quantities, typically with all stages of manufacture carried out by themselves.<ref name=cooper>Emmanuel Cooper, ''Ten Thousand Years of Pottery''. [[British Museum Press]], 2000. {{ISBN|0-7141-2701-9}}.</ref> [[Studio pottery]] includes functional wares such as [[tableware]], [[Cookware and bakeware|cookware]] and non-functional wares such as [[sculpture]]. Studio potters can be referred to as ceramic artists, ceramists, ceramicists or as an artist who uses clay as a medium.
