{{Infobox University | name = Pandit Lakhmi Chand State University of Performing and Visual Arts, Rohtak | image_name = Supvarohtaklogo.png | motto = | mottoeng = | established = 2014 | type = [[Public Universities|Public]] | chancellor = [[Governor of Haryana]] | vice_chancellor = Rajbir Singh | provost = [[Registrar (education)|Registrar]] | city = [[Rohtak]] | state = [[Haryana]] | country = [[India]] | coor = {{coord|28|54|31|N|76|36|24|E|type:edu_region:IN|display=inline}} | campus = [[urban area|Urban]], {{convert|22|acre|km2|1|abbr=on}} |colors = {{scarf|{{cells|3|#D58063}}{{cell|#EFD8CA}}{{cells|3|#D58063}}{{cell|#EFD8CA}}{{cells|3|#D58063}}}} | students = | Hostel = | free_label = | free = | affiliations = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ugc.ac.in/oldpdf/State%20University/Consolidated%20List%20of%20State%20Universities%20as%20on%2011-09-2015.pdf|title=List of State Universities Under UGC|date=11 September 2015|accessdate=11 September 2015|publisher=www.ugc.ac.in}}</ref> | website = '''http://supva.ac.in'''
}}
'''Pandit Lakhmi Chand State University of Performing and Visual Arts''' (PSUPVA), is a university in [[Rohtak]], [[India]].<ref name="GTIS to Supva">{{cite web | url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/chandigarh/bills-passed-for-three-new-universities/article1-1240474.aspx | title=Bills passed for three new universities | publisher=Hindustantimes | accessdate=15 July 2014}}</ref> It is a joint campus of four institutions: [[State Institute of Film and Television]] , [[State Institute of Design]],<ref name=SID>{{cite web | url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/now-clothes-from-discarded-cassette-reels-with-pix-114093000440_1.html | title=Now, clothes from discarded cassette reels | publisher=Business Standard | accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> [[State Institute of Fine Arts]] and [[State Institute of Urban Planning and Architecture]].
==History== It was established in 2014 university by the [[Government of Haryana]] with the name ''Pandit Lakhmi Chand State University of Performing and Visual Arts'',<ref name="GTIS to Supva"/> which was renamed to the ''Pandit Lakhmi Chand State University of Performing and Visual Arts'' on 15 November 2018 by the cabinet committee of the Haryana state.<ref name=cab1>[http://www.uniindia.com/haryana-cabinet-issues-ordinance-to-change-name-of-state-university-of-performing-and-visual-arts/north/news/1405847.html University name changed], The Tribune, 15 Nov 2018.</ref> Ar. Ashwani Sabharwal<ref name="VC of SUPVA">{{cite web | url=http://www.punjabkhabar.com/news/800-ashwani-kumar-takes-over-as-vice-chancellor-of-state-university-of-performing-and-visual-arts.aspx | title=Ashwani Kumar takes over as Vice Chancellor of State University of Performing and Visual Arts | publisher=Punjabkhabar | accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> was appointed as the first Vice Chancellor of the University.
Currently, IAS officer V.S. Kundu is the current Vice- Chancellor of the university.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://supva.ac.in/supva.ac.in/index/message-from-vice-chancellor.html|title=Message from Vice Chancellor|last=Admin|first=Super|website=supva.ac.in|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-12-26}}</ref>[http://supva.ac.in/supva.ac.in/index/message-from-vice-chancellor.html]
